# Technology Stack

This document outlines the technology stack used in the Fleetyards
application.

## Backend

- **Ruby**: 3.4.x
- **Ruby on Rails**: 7.2.x
- **PostgreSQL**: Database management system
- **Redis**: For caching and Sidekiq job queue
- **Sidekiq**: Background job processing
- **Devise**: Authentication (with OAuth via OmniAuth)
- **Action Policy**: Authorization
- **RSpec**: Testing framework (with rswag for API specs)
- **FactoryBot**: Test data generation

## Frontend

- **Vue.js 3**: Frontend framework
- **TypeScript**: Type safety for JavaScript
- **Vite.js**: Build tool and dev server
- **SCSS/Sass**: CSS preprocessor
- **Tanstack Vue Query**: Data fetching library
- **Pinia**: State management (with persisted state plugin)
- **Orval**: API client and TypeScript type generation from OpenAPI schema

## Development Tools

- **Docker & Docker Compose**: Containerization
- **ESLint**: JavaScript/TypeScript linting
- **Prettier**: Code formatting
- **StandardRB**: Ruby code linting
- **Playwright**: End-to-end testing

## Deployment & Infrastructure

- **GitHub Actions**: CI/CD
- **Appsignal**: Performance monitoring

## External Services

- **ImageMagick**: Image manipulation

## Requirements

- **PostgreSQL**: Database
- **Redis**: Caching and job queue
- **imagemagick**: Image manipulation
